content.div:
I've decided there is just too much to talk about around CC for me to do it alone (you should see how many draft entries are waiting to be finished!) So I've invited some other people who are involved with CCau to contribute as well. Say hello to:
Jessica Coates, Project Manager, Creative Commons Clinic;
Nic Suzor, who doing his PhD on virtual environments;
Rachel Cobcroft, who is currently developing case studies of projects and individuals using CC in Australia and is doing her PhD on motiviations for sharing on Flickr;
Emma Carroll, who is interested in CC and the music industry; and
Isha Baywaters, who took the Creative Commons Clinic course and is currently researching open business models for the music industry.
Looking forward to their ideas!
Of course, this is not an official CCau blog, it is the personal ideas and opinions of people involved with CCau.
